3 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
4 INDICATED.
5 (2) “ASSIGNING FEES” MEANS THE FEES CHARGED BY AN ASSIGNOR.
6 (3) “ASSIGNOR” MEANS AN OFFICIATING ASSOCIATION OR
7 ORGANIZATION OR AN INDEPENDENT CONTRACTOR THAT:
8 (I) IS REGISTERED AND IN GOOD STANDING WITH THE STATE
9 DEPARTMENT OF ASSESSMENTS AND TAXATION; AND
10 (II) PROVIDES, ASSIGNS, AND SCHEDULES THE OFFICIALS THAT
11 PROVIDE THE HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING SERVICES FOR A HIGH SCHOOL
12 SPORTING EVENT.
13 (2) “HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIAL” MEANS AN OFFICIAL, AN
14 UMPIRE, A REFEREE, OR A JUDGE WHO PRESIDES OVER A SPORTING EVENT TO
15 GUARANTEE THAT THE RULES OF THE EVENT ARE ENFORCED.
16 (3) “HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING ROLE” MEANS AN
17 OFFICIATING ASSIGNMENT FOR A HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIAL THAT REQUIRES
18 PERFORMANCE OF A DEFINED SET OF HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING
19 SERVICES.
20 (4) “HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING SERVICES” MEANS THE
21 OFFICIATING SERVICES PROVIDED BY AN OFFICIAL, AN UMPIRE, A REFEREE, OR A
22 JUDGE AT A HIGH SCHOOL SPORTING EVENT A HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIAL
23 WHEN OVERSEEING A HIGH SCHOOL SPORT.
24 (5) “SIMILAR BOYS’ AND GIRLS’ HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS” MEANS HIGH
25 SCHOOL SPORTS THAT:
26 (I) OCCUR IN THE SAME SEASON;
27 (II) HAVE COMPARABLE RULES;
28 (III) HAVE A SIMILAR NUMBER OF HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS
29 OFFICIALS; AND
30 (IV) HAVE A SIMILAR TIME OF COMPETITION.

