1 (2) IN CATEGORIZING BOYS’ AND GIRLS’ SPORTS AS SIMILAR, THE
2 DEPARTMENT SHALL CONSIDER WHETHER EACH SPORT:
3 (I) OCCURS IN THE SAME SEASON;
4 (II) HAS COMPARABLE RULES;
5 (III) REQUIRES A SIMILAR NUMBER OF HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS
6 OFFICIALS;
7 (IV) REQUIRES SIMILAR HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING
8 SERVICES; AND
9 (V) FEATURES COMPETITION OF COMPARABLE LENGTHS OF
10 TIME.
11 (3) THE DEPARTMENT, IN CONSULTATION WITH THE MARYLAND
12 PUBLIC SECONDARY SCHOOLS ATHLETIC ASSOCIATION, SHALL UPDATE THE LIST
13 EVERY 3 YEARS.
14 (C) (1) THIS SUBSECTION APPLIES TO A HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIAL
15 WHO:
16 (I) IS AN EMPLOYEE OF THE LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM; OR
17 (II) IS EMPLOYED BY AN INDEPENDENT CONTRACTOR OR
18 OFFICIATING ASSOCIATION OR ORGANIZATION, WITH WHICH THE COUNTY BOARD
19 CONTRACTS.
20 (2) A COUNTY BOARD SHALL ENSURE THAT HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS
21 OFFICIALS RECEIVE THE SAME PAY IF THE OFFICIALS:
22 (I) ARE IN SIMILAR HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING
23 ROLES; AND
24 (II) ARE PROVIDING OFFICIATING SERVICES FOR SPORTS
25 CATEGORIZED AS SIMILAR UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION.
26 (D) (1) A COUNTY BOARD SHALL REJECT A BID OR PROPOSAL FOR A
27 PROCUREMENT CONTRACT THAT WOULD RESULT IN DIFFERENT PAY OR FEES FOR
28 HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIALS IN A SIMILAR HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING
29 ROLE FOR SPORTS CATEGORIZED AS SIMILAR UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS
30 SECTION.

HOUSE BILL 1483 5
1 (2) WHEN SOLICITING INVITATIONS FOR A BID OR A REQUEST FOR A
2 PROPOSAL FOR HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING SERVICES, A COUNTY BOARD
3 SHALL SOLICIT BIDS OR REQUESTS FOR A PROPOSAL FOR EACH SPORT WITHIN A
4 REASONABLE TIME OF THE SOLICITATION OF BIDS OR REQUESTS FOR PROPOSALS
5 FOR ALL SPORTS CATEGORIZED AS SIMILAR UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS
6 SECTION.
7 (E) (1) THIS SECTION MAY ONLY BE CONSTRUED TO REQUIRE PARITY
8 BETWEEN HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIALS PERFORMING SIMILAR ROLES IN
9 SIMILAR SPORTS WITHIN A COUNTY AND MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED TO REQUIRE
10 PARITY IN HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIALS BETWEEN COUNTIES.
11 (2) THIS SECTION MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED TO HAVE ANY EFFECT ON
12 THE GROUPING OF SPORTS TOGETHER FOR ANY PURPOSE OTHER THAN THE
13 PAYMENT OF HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIALS OR FEES ASSIGNED TO CONTRACTS
14 FOR HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIALS.
15 (3) THIS SECTION MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED TO PROHIBIT FEES
16 OUTSIDE OF A PROCUREMENT CONTRACT AS A BONUS TO HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS
17 OFFICIALS.
18 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That:
19 (a) A local school system that executed a procurement contract for high school
20 sports officiating services, as defined in § 4–147 of the Education Article, as enacted by
21 Section 1 of this Act, on or before July 1, 2025, may extend the term of the contract to align
22 the contract timelines for similar boys’ and girls’ high school sports.
23 (b) A local school system may not extend a contract under subsection (a) of this
24 section beyond July 1, 2029.
25 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, except for a contract for high
26 school sports officials extended by a local school system in accordance with Section 2 of this
27 Act, this Act shall be construed to apply only prospectively and may not be applied or
28 interpreted to have any effect on or application to any procurement contracts for high school
29 sports officiating services, as defined in § 4–147 of the Education Article, as enacted under
30 Section 1 of this Act, entered into before the effective date of this Act.
31 SECTION 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
32 1, 2025.

